---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="The mission, name, and story behind Restore the Last.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-white section-padding border-b border-primary/10">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="label text-primary mb-4">About</p>
      <div class="gold-line mb-8"></div>
      <h1 class="text-dark text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-bold leading-tight max-w-3xl">
        We exist for the people the system forgot.
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mission Statement -->
  <section class="bg-offwhite section-padding">
    <div class="container-narrow max-w-3xl">
      <p class="label text-primary mb-6">Our Mission</p>
      <p class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl text-dark leading-relaxed">
        Millions of trauma survivors live with nervous systems that won't stop fighting — even after the danger is gone. We know how to help.
      </p>
      <p class="text-body text-lg mt-8 leading-relaxed">
        Restore the Last funds frontline organizations with neurofeedback technology to deliver nervous system restoration to those who need it most — including survivors of trafficking, foster care, and violence. The problem is massive. The solution exists. We just need to get it to the right people.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Name -->
  <section class="bg-light section-padding">
    <div class="container-narrow max-w-3xl">
      <p class="label text-primary mb-6">Our Name</p>
      <h2 class="mb-10">Restore the Last</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-primary/10">
          <h3 class="text-xl mb-3 text-primary">Restore</h3>
          <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
            From Psalm 23 — "He restores my soul." The Hebrew word is <em>yashuv</em>: to return, to bring back, to make whole again. Not to fix what's broken, but to recover what was always there. That's what nervous system restoration does. It doesn't add something new. It returns the brain to the calm it was built for.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-primary/10">
          <h3 class="text-xl mb-3 text-primary">The Last</h3>
          <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
            From Matthew 20:16 — "The last shall be first." And Matthew 25 — "Whatever you did for the least of these, you did for me." The last are the ones forgotten by the system. The ones who aged out. The ones trafficked. The ones born into violence they didn't choose. We start there.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- North Stars -->
  <section class="bg-offwhite section-padding">
    <div class="container-narrow max-w-3xl">
      <p class="label text-primary mb-6">North Stars</p>
      <h2 class="mb-10">What guides us.</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-primary/10">
          <h3 class="text-xl mb-3">Psalm 23</h3>
          <p class="font-serif italic text-primary text-lg mb-4">"He restores my soul."</p>
          <p class="text-body">
            We believe in restoration — not management, not coping, not endurance. The nervous system can heal. That conviction drives everything we fund.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-primary/10">
          <h3 class="text-xl mb-3">Tikkun Olam</h3>
          <p class="font-serif italic text-primary text-lg mb-4">"Repair of the world."</p>
          <p class="text-body">
            A Jewish concept that calls us to participate in mending what's broken. Not wait for someone else. Not study the problem longer. Act — where the fracture is deepest.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How We Work -->
  <section class="bg-white section-padding">
    <div class="container-narrow max-w-3xl">
      <p class="label text-primary mb-6">How We Work</p>
      <h2 class="mb-8">We fund. We don't run clinics.</h2>
      <p class="text-body text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Restore the Last is deployment infrastructure. We raise funds, place neurofeedback technology into partner facilities, train staff, and measure outcomes. We don't operate treatment centers. We equip the ones that already exist — with technology they couldn't access on their own.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-light rounded-2xl p-6 border-l-4 border-primary">
        <p class="text-body text-sm">
          <strong>Note:</strong> Restore the Last and CalmWaves are legally and operationally separate organizations. CalmWaves develops the direct neurofeedback technology. Restore the Last funds its deployment to those who need it most.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founding Team -->
  <section class="bg-offwhite section-padding">
    <div class="container-narrow max-w-4xl">
      <p class="label text-primary mb-6">Founding Team</p>
      <h2 class="mb-4">Built by people who've seen the proof.</h2>
      <p class="text-body text-lg leading-relaxed mb-12 max-w-3xl">
        Restore the Last wasn't built in a boardroom. It was built by two people who watched this technology change lives — and couldn't justify not doing something about it.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">

        <!-- Dallas -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-primary/10">
          <div class="w-20 h-20 rounded-full bg-light border border-primary/10 mb-6 overflow-hidden">
            <div class="w-full h-full flex items-center justify-center text-primary/30 text-xs font-bold">Photo</div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-bold mb-1">Dallas Cowan</h3>
          <p class="label text-gold mb-4">Co-Founder, Operations</p>
          <p class="text-body text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Dallas leads the operational side of Restore the Last — partner development, program design, and deployment strategy. He has worked directly with kids in the foster care system and has seen firsthand the gap between what these populations need and what the system provides.
          </p>
          <p class="text-body text-sm leading-relaxed">
            He has also been on the ground helping build brain health and performance centers across the country alongside CalmWaves — which means he understands both the technology and the organizational infrastructure needed to scale it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Dr. Doug -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-primary/10">
          <div class="w-20 h-20 rounded-full bg-light border border-primary/10 mb-6 overflow-hidden">
            <div class="w-full h-full flex items-center justify-center text-primary/30 text-xs font-bold">Photo</div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-bold mb-1">Dr. Doug Cowan</h3>
          <p class="label text-gold mb-4">Co-Founder</p>
          <p class="text-body text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Dr. Doug Cowan is a licensed therapist with over 30,000 brain improvement sessions to his name. His clinical work spans veterans, trauma survivors, PTSD, and people that traditional mental health care has struggled to reach. That body of work is the foundation this organization stands on.
          </p>
          <p class="text-body text-sm leading-relaxed">
            He is also the founder of <a href="https://calmwaves.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary font-bold hover:text-medium transition-colors">CalmWaves</a> — the organization behind the direct neurofeedback technology we deploy. Restore the Last exists to get that technology to the people who need it most.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Board of Directors -->
  <section class="bg-white section-padding">
    <div class="container-narrow max-w-3xl">
      <p class="label text-primary mb-6">Board of Directors</p>
      <h2 class="mb-6">Taking shape.</h2>
      <p class="text-body text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        We are currently forming our board of directors as we build toward full 501(c)(3) status. We are looking for people who bring expertise in nonprofit governance, trauma-informed care, faith-based community, fundraising, or international development — and who share the conviction that this work matters.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-light rounded-2xl p-6 border border-primary/10 border-l-4 border-l-primary">
        <h4 class="font-serif font-bold mb-2">Interested in joining the board?</h4>
        <p class="text-body text-sm mb-4">
          If you're passionate about this mission and have experience you'd like to contribute, we'd love to hear from you.
        </p>
        <a href="mailto:dallas@restorethelast.org?subject=Board of Directors Inquiry" class="btn-primary text-sm">Reach out →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-deep text-white section-padding text-center">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-white text-3xl mb-6">The solution exists. We fund the distance.</h2>
      <a href="/give" class="btn-gold text-lg">Partner with us</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
